{{Quote|One of my Jedi students was of the Vrassh. He had a great deal of anger to work through before his training could properly begin.|Luke Skywalker|<ref name="SotP">''[[Specter of the Past]]''</ref>}}
The '''Vrassh''' were victims of a genocidal act known as the [[Vrassh Slaughter]]. Despite the requirements of [[Pas'sic]] law, the survivors of the Vrassh slaughter had been compensated by neither the [[Pas'sic (group)|Pas'sic]] nor the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] as of [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]].<ref name="SotP" />

[[Unidentified Vrassh Jedi|One of the students]] at [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker's]] [[Jedi Praxeum]] was of the Vrassh. He had to learn to deal with the anger he felt over the victimization of his people before beginning his training.<ref name="SotP" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Vrassh are mentioned in the novel ''[[Specter of the Past]]'', written by [[Timothy Zahn]]. From the context, it is unclear whether the term refers to the people of a particular [[Planet/Legends|planet]], a [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] [[Species/Legends|species]], or some other [[organization]].<ref name="SotP" />

